  "instructions": [
    "Heat the oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion, carrot, and celery and cook until the vegetables are softened, about 8 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the cumin, caraway seeds, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper, and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the aubergine and cook for 5 minutes, until it begins to soften.",
    "Add the braised beef (if using), beef broth, diced tomatoes, and tomato paste, and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes, or until the aubergine is tender.",
    "Stir in the sour cream, feta cheese, parsley, chives, and dill, and season with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve the borshch hot, garnished with shredded cabbage, chopped fresh herbs, and a dollop of sour cream, if desired.",
    "To make the croutons, preheat the oven to 350\u00182F (180\u001aC).",
    "Cut the bread into small cubes and toss with the shortening, salt, pepper, vinegar, and olive oil until the bread is evenly coated.",
    "Spread the bread cubes on a baking sheet and bake for 10-15 minutes, or until crispy and golden brown.",
    "Toss the croutons with the baking powder and water until they are evenly coated.",
    "Stir the croutons into the borshch just before serving.",
    "Serve the borshch hot, garnished with croutons and a dollop of sour cream, if desired."
  ],
